g areas. There's a minor inconsistency where s4 removes the abbreviated comment markers from the source XML, but overall the file appears sound with only a slight semantic shift in how ORDER BY specifications are characterized. the knowledge file actually strips out that `<!-- 中略 -->` comment, making the XML appear complete when it's not—this could mislead an AI into thinking there are no additional properties, even though the source clearly indicates there are more configuration options further down. I'm seeing a table with configuration values like stringValue, numberValue, and dateValue that the knowledge file doesn't include, but since those same values appear in the XML example itself, there's no actual information loss. The main concern is that removing the `<!-- 中略 -->` comment makes the XML look complete when it's actually abbreviated, which could mislead someone into using it as a full configuration template. I'll flag this as a minor omission and mark the overall status as having issues.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16863,"cache_read_input_tokens":18561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":16863,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"409a4fc0-7d9d-4768-885e-d4911dff334e","uuid":"47ae0490-072a-43bb-b35d-51f219c155bf"}
